# doc2video-ml-engine

ML Engine for Document → Video pipeline (full engine: summarization, scene-splitting, prompt generation, TTS, Pika API glue, assembly).

## What this repo contains
- PDF/text extractor
- LLM summarizer & scene/story generator
- Scene → video prompt generator
- Face encoder / style transfer hooks
- Pika API interface (text -> video)
- TTS interface (ElevenLabs)
- Video assembler using MoviePy
- Example script & sample data

## Quick start (local)
1. Clone repo
2. `python3 -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate`
3. `pip install -r requirements.txt`
4. Copy your API keys into `config.yml`
5. Put a sample file at `example_data/sample_upload.png` (or reference `/mnt/data/90133d28-3792-4719-868f-11bc0181fbf0.png`)
6. Run:
   ```bash
   bash run_example.sh

